results.name: Numbers k such that (266*10^k + 1)/3 is prime.
comment: Numbers k such that digits 88 followed by k-1 occurrences of digit 6 followed by the digit 7 is prime (see Example section).
example: 6 is in this sequence because (266*10^n+1)/3 = 88666667 is prime.
program: (MAGMA) [n: n in [0..220] | IsPrime((266*10^n + 1) div 3)]; // _Vincenzo Librandi_, Feb 23 2016
results.author: _Robert Price_, Feb 22 2016
